data.name: Nikhil Patil
data.caption: Ex-Fractal | University of Florida
data.bio: Passionate about merging design thinking with software development. My journey in technology is driven by a deep commitment to understanding user challenges and crafting intuitive solutions that not only solve problems but also delight users. With a focus on customer-centric design, I aim to transform complex issues into simple, effective software experiences.

info: Delivered a AI powered product for Unilever to identify non-profitable SKUs in their portfolio across markets like EU, US, NAMET, AFRICA, ASIA, and LATAM saving approximately $85M in expenses.
Performed ETL using Azure Databricks, Python, py-spark, SQL, and scheduled notebooks in Azure Data Factory. Used Azure Synapse Analytics for big data and data warehousing solutions.
Researched user pain points in the legacy systems and improved engagement by working on more than 10 user stories.
Transformed the legacy system to a microservice architecture using Spring Boot and AWS resulting in a 40% boost in system availability.
Built dashboarding screens using React-Native and Charts.js that focused on customer engagement and communicating concise insights.
Implemented multi-threaded modules in Java Spring Boot, to concurrently fetch and process 10+ performance indicators using REST APIs reducing the time to render data from 1.3 sec to 0.5 sec.

projects.name: Greedy Algorithms and Dynamic Programming
info: Programming projects to solve peculiar problems constrained by time and space complexities
Performing analysis and comparative study between optimal and sub-optimal approaches via charts and graphs.

projects.name: Disease Prediction using Machine Learning
info: This Machine Learning project is used to predict diseases based on the symptoms given by the user.
It predicts using three different machine learning algorithms.It uses tkinter for GUI.
The model harnesses an extensive array of 95 symptoms to accurately predict outcomes across 41 distinct diseases.

data.name: Supril Singh
data.caption: Ex-Coinbase | University of Florida
data.bio: I'm a results-driven Graduate Student passionate about solving complex challenges with innovative solutions. Currently pursuing my Master's at the University of Florida, I've navigated dynamic roles as a Senior Software Engineer at Coinbase, seamlessly transitioning to Data Scientist. My diverse background bridges development and data science, empowering teams with actionable insights. Eager to merge academic excellence with real-world experiences, I thrive on continuous learning and collaboration.

info: Worked on building automated pipelines for extracting, processing, embedding text data from 2 major SDLC platforms.
Used Java and Python to develop REST APIs to access the ML models, maintained postman collection and documented the APIs.
Implemented ML models for 4 use cases: Text Clustering, Correlation, Summarization and Semantic Search Engine.
Designed Microservice Architecture, Database Schemas and developed REST APIs, wireframes as well as UI for the application.
Automated Swagger UI generation upon detecting changes in the Git repository, resulting in a 95% reduction in manual efforts.
Migrated on-premises application to the Cloud and setup CI/CD Pipeline, leading to a 30% decrease in deployment time.

projects.name: Chatwave: Full Stack Web Application
info: Actively developing a MERN full-stack social media platform on AWS, incorporating best practices like global error handling and logging and caching.
Implementing features such as infinite scrolling and messaging for an enhanced user experience.

Implementing Infrastructure as Code using Terraform, facilitating efficient environment management, and orchestrated a robust CI/CD pipeline, integrating Terraform seamlessly for continuous deployment.

projects.name: Comment Generation for Source Code: VS Code Extension
info: VS Code extension to streamline comment generation for code files, with support for 6 languages, to generate informative comments that summarize the functionality and purpose of the code.
Wrote the extension in Node, which triggers an API request to any one of the 6 models hosted in flask, to generate comment.

projects.name: GatorLibrary: Efficient Library Management System
info: Designed and implemented a library management system in C++ utilizing Heaps and Red-Black Trees to ensure efficient book tracking and patron management.
Applied Object-Oriented Programming principles to structure the project, incorporating features such as book borrowing, returning, ranged searches, and flip count tracking.

data.name: Bob Johnson
data.caption: Data Scientist | Data Analyst
data.bio: Passionate about extracting insights from data and leveraging them to drive business decisions.

info: Analyzed large datasets to identify trends and patterns for actionable insights.
Created interactive dashboards and reports to communicate findings to stakeholders.

projects.name: Customer Segmentation
info: Performed customer segmentation analysis to identify target customer groups.
Utilized clustering algorithms to group customers based on purchasing behavior.

data.name: Emily Brown
data.caption: UX/UI Designer | Frontend Developer
data.bio: Passionate about creating intuitive user experiences through thoughtful design and development.

info: Collaborated with cross-functional teams to conceptualize and design user interfaces.
Conducted user research and usability testing to iterate and improve design solutions.

projects.name: Mobile App Redesign
info: Redesigned the user interface of a mobile app to improve usability and aesthetics.
Implemented user feedback to enhance the overall user experience.

data.name: Harsh Reddy
data.caption: Ex-Software Developer @ TCS · MSCS @ UF
data.bio: Experienced system engineer adept at crafting seamless integrations and optimizing complex systems. Skilled in software development, with a focus on backend solutions and client-centric approaches. Passionate about leveraging technology to drive efficiency and solve real-world challenges.

info: As the Lead Software Developer in my team, I spearheaded a time-critical project focused on establishing a seamless connection between NASDAQ.
System Integration: Developed and optimized a utility tool to seamlessly connect NASDAQ and the Reserve Bank of India for the Clearing Corporation of India Project.
Database Expertise: Utilized Oracle Toad and Postgres databases to support daily financial market transactions
Spearheaded the creation of efficient and responsive backend deployments tailored to client demands.

Engineered and executed the deployment of production servers, driving optimization of legacy code. This resulted in a substantial 5-billion-dollar boost in trade processing efficiency across 1600 trades.

projects.name: Admission Portal Web Application
info: Designed a web application to facilitate the admission of students to universities. Portal devises a merit list of students and assigns seats based on that.
Achieved high throughput on SQL server by handling assignments for over 1000 student records, across 10 universities.

projects.name: Gossip Algorithm
info: The algorithm measures the convergence time of gossip in a distributed network of nodes under different topologies like full, line, 2d, and 3d.

data.name: Emily Johnson
data.caption: Web Developer Intern | CS @ UF
data.bio: I am Emily Johnson, a dedicated software engineer fueled by a passion for crafting innovative solutions. Currently pursuing a Bachelor's in Computer Science and hands-on experience in full-stack development and machine learning, I thrive in dynamic tech environments. My journey is defined by a commitment to leveraging my expertise to tackle complex challenges and drive impactful change.

info: Performed Semantic Analysis on Spark SQL statements & optimized average query execution runtime by 15%.
Engineered a holistic web interface, enabling users to perform semantic analysis with more than 8 parameters.
Orchestrated technical architecture (technology stack, data flow, database, deployment, REST APIs) of a Packaging Service.
Developed 20+ RESTful APIs for logging, regenerating, and approving data packages with metadata across 4 departments.

projects.name: Aptitude Test Quiz App
info: Built a user-friendly Android application with wide range of test questions across 4 test domains, featuring 3 difficulty levels for each domain enabling users to take timed tests, analyze their scores, and track their progress over time

projects.name: Stock Prediction Model
info: Created a highly configurable analytic dashboard for researchers working on correlation of sentiment analysis and data analytics to predict stock market trends for over 30 companies.

info: Finding systematic ways to identify and trace outliers in Liquidity Coverage Ratio data.
Evaluated statistical methods like Z-Score, Isolation Forest and Interquartile Range to find the best fit for financial data.
Video analytics for real time feed.
Implemented analytics code on docker containers.
Worked on hosting models on Triton Inference Server.

projects.tech: NLP · SVM · Machine Learning · Deep Learning
info: Trend analysis and link prediction on original dataset of around 110K entries.
Integrated Federated Healthcare Platform: Topic modelling on original dataset. Worked on NER and keyword based search.

projects.name: Text to SQL
info: Focused on developing a text-to-SQL conversion system using state-of-the-art Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques
This involved extensive data preprocessing, including tokenization and semantic analysis, as well as model training using advanced neural network architectures
